      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the elusive sourdough starter! It sounds like your kitchen is a bit chilly for a lively sourdough. The yeast and bacteria in your starter need a warm environment to thrive, ideally around 75-80 degrees Fahrenheit. Try moving your starter to a warmer spot, like near a radiator or in an oven with the light on, for a few hours. Also, make sure you're feeding it with equal parts flour and water, and give it a good stir. Keep an eye out for bubbles, and in a few days, you should see some signs of life. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
